# Model Madness - Supabase Configuration (OPTIONAL)
#
# Supabase provides persistent state so all viewers see the same scores,
# even when ESPN's API is unavailable. Without these, the site falls back
# to polling ESPN directly (which works fine for most cases).
#
# Get these from your Supabase project settings:
# Dashboard > Settings > API

# Your Supabase project URL (set in Vercel Environment Variables)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Anon key (safe to expose client-side, used with RLS)
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# Service role key (KEEP SECRET - only for server-side admin updates)
# This is NOT used in the static site, only if you set up a cron job
# to sync ESPN -> Supabase on a schedule
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
